character
Their parents David and Jill
It all started with a row with their parents,
JILL I am fed up with you telling me who to go out with I am not a two year old I can make up my own mind without asking you what to do
PARENTS that will be enough from you my girl or else you'll find yourself in bed, I just had enough of you my girl,
JILL Well I am going to pack my bag and move out
PARENTS If you move out you'll never come in this house again
JILL Well that's good enough for me, I'll be out in an hour
PARENTS When you get out you can stay out
JILL that's good
Jill ran upstairs to pack a case she came down, put on her coat and went out of the front door
PARENTS She's not coming back in this house whatever happens
Jill went to her boyfriend's house, she rang the door bell David opened the door
DAVID What are you doing here ? I was just coming round to your house to see if you could put me up for the night, I have had a row with my parents
They told me to get out
JILL So have my parents
DAVID Let's go and get married, that's if you want to married
JILL Of course I do
DAVID Well let's go and get married then we can get a flat or something Well they got married and got a house
They live happily ever after
The End

