TWO PEOPLE CHARACTERS Jean Joyce
SCENE I Two teenager girls at the top of the village when a boy comes along and asks them for a date at seven O'clock
The boy's name is John seagull
The two girls are mucking about on the top road
The boy was going by on a motor bike
He stops and leans his motor bike by the shelter wall and said "Why was you playing on the road, haven't you got a boyfriend" (he said it to Joyce because she was the prettiest ) and Joyce said "No I haven't got a boyfriend boyfriend" The boy said "oh" Do you want to come out with me because I haven't got a girl friend," this was about 3
30 one Sunday afternoon
in the winter
The boy said "shall we go for a walk
Joyce still hadn't answered his question
So he asked her again
So Joyce said I would like to
Now I will have something to do in the evening
Joyce said I am glad I am going out with you because it was boring sitting at home in the evening doing nothing
Jean already had a boyfriend she was waiting for her boyfriend to come he has a car
Joyce said here comes Roy Jean
John said
" Whoever's Roy, Joyce said that is Jean's boyfriend
They never did go for a walk
Joyce said shall we go home John said "if you like and so they went home Joyce said to Jean see you tonight" Cheerio for now
Joyce has no brothers or sisters
Joyce's parents said whoever's this with Joyce
Joyce introduced John to her parents they said glad to meet you
John said shall we go to the pictures
Joyce said yes can Roy and Jean come if you want so Joyce and John walked down the road to Jean's house
he asked Jean and she said yes please
So Roy said shall we go in the car
So they said if you like, "John said I will pay for you to go to the pictures
Roy said "What time are we going
