Bob was just going to take the money and James dropped it
Bob bent down to pick it up
That's what James was waiting for he hit Bob on the head and knocked him out
James and his friends picked him up and put him in the car
The police realized that James had found out that Bob told them about James and the gang
James and his friend drove off in their car with Bob lying in a heap in the floor of the car
The police had got James car number and they were hot on the trail of them
Bob was just coming to, he pull himself up and looked out of the back window he could see the police car behind
James had not seen the police car behind they pulled up at a house they took Bob in the house
The police stopped near the house two policemen went round the back and knocked on the door when the policemen knocked at the door James and his friends looked out back windows, Then the police went in the front door James was coming down the stairs the police caught James and his friends , they all got 10 years for robbery
Bob had a lump on his head for a week but he got 50# reward
The End

Caught red handed
One day Tom an old tramp was walking up a hill, it was getting dark and it was very cold
It must have been freezing hard for there was icicles hanging from gutter of houses , the snow on ground was crisp as he walked through the village
Tom saw a light coming from a farmhouse it did not look far
Old, Tom jumped a ditch and walked towards the light he arrived at farm
He could see a barn he went in and in corner there was a heap of straw in another there was a heap of potatoes and he could see a rabbit locker
He walked over to it there was rabbit in it but he could not see how many there was
He went back to the straw lay down and went to sleep
Next morning he was up at 4 am it was dark then he thought he had better go before the farmer got but he did not go empty handed he took two of the farmer's rabbits and some potatoes in a bag
He walked about a mile
Old Tom's legs began to ache so he stopped he was in a brussels field most of them were picked, it was just getting light
Tom put the two rabbits and potatoes down
He sat down and thought to himself how can I light a fire he looked round the field and he saw to his delight a hide made from bale he walked over to them there was some strikes and a tin the tin had some diesel in it
Tom did not lose any time in making a fire he got an old tin out of the hedge and put it the fire he put some snow in it picked 3 or 4 brussels and got 2 old potatoes and put in the tin with his brussels and the rabbit were also cooked on the fire
Tom enjoyed his food that night he went back for some more
He did not know the farmer was waiting for him
He went in the barn and shut the door the farmer was on the loft
