He said it fed all right for the first three days, but now she won't feed at all
So I said let me come and look at her , so we went and had a look at her , and she was lame on the her right, front leg
I said to Bill no wonder she does not feed very well, she is lame on her front leg
Bill said she will not feed at all , well let me see the kind of grub you give her then
So Bill showed me, I said don't you give the old girl any bran no said bill well there you are that is your trouble then I said
You give her some bran tonight and then see if she will eat it
Well I could give her some now couldn't I yes if you wish Look at that see she will eat it now yes thanks John, that's all right mate
She is in pig isn't she Bill yes she should have them on the 24th June
Well I know one thing what you want to do
What is that John, you want to clean her out and put her plenty of straw in the place where she sleeps and out in the yard

The Old Bull
One day I went round old man Jones's farm and he and some of his workmen had got the bull out in the yard
As I went in the gate the old bull started to turn on me, so old man Jones, said get behind that old cart Joe
About 4 or 5 minutes after, I came out from behind the cart
They had got the old bull back in the shed
Then he asked me if I would help him bring daisy the old cow up to go with the old bull, because he thinks that she ought to have a nothing calf
So he put her in with old Toogey the bull he got on her back and we let him stay with her for about half of an hour
About four to five month after she had been with the old bull she had a calf it was a bull calf
When it was about ten weeks old, when we sold it it made #1510s6d
Then the time came for the old bull to be sold he was too old and fat for the old cows
So we took him down tonbury market and he made #8510/6d alive he weighed one and a half tons

