One day I was walking down the street there was a little mole I picked it up and took it home it had caught its leg in a trap and broken it it got better in a few weeks time but I set it free after a few days
It came back I built it a hutch with a lot of mud and grass
It liked that place very much I tried to find anther mole I found one it was quite big I did not know whether it was a male or a female but put them together they did not fight after a few months she has some babies four little ones they were very sweet and they never wanted to leave me and hutch I built for them I gave them worms and water and a few breadcrumbs it never ate very much at all they lived nicely in their little hutch until they all died of old age

I am writing a story about what I do in the summer Holiday when it is hot I go swimming and when it isn't so hot I go to find some wild insects last year I had some frogspawn
I have some every year and only a few die
It is quite hard to find a place for I keep my frog spawn underneath the tank where I it is very cool it takes about 3 months to get ? first they get long then they grow their fins and after a few weeks they get bigger and bigger
but last year there wasn't very many eggs around I went to the moat first there weren't any there so I went down the lane but near the white bridge there was only about 50 eggs
I got down and picked them up with my hands and put them in a big jar with some sea weed they must have a large tin or a large jar not a small thing otherwise when the tadpoles grow they have not much room to move I use a big paint tin to put my frog spawn in and when they get to be frogs and at the end of my garden their is a stream I climb down the back and tip the frogs in the water and you can just watch them swim away
It is best to tip the frogs away when they just lose their tail then you know they will live and just one other thing you must keep them clean and their sea weed every week and they will like a bit of rough meat to chew and that will keep them alive

