the mystery castle
One day there were two men they were very greedy and selfish they heard something about a castle
one day in the middle of a big lake they decided to explore it
they did not know it had a witch living in it
they borrowed a rowing boat and sailed right to the middle of the lake and when they got near the castle they saw a signpost sticking up from the water it had beware of this castle there is a horrid old witch the men did not worry about the signpost they just went rowing on when they got nearer to the castle they saw another signpost which had a skeleton the men were a bit frightened of this they didn't know what it meant
they saw four girls in a boat with a cloak and hood and with a mask on their face
their names were the four spy girls they knew how to get in the mystery castle
the girls did not see the men
they hid round the other side
the men did not see what they were doing so they rowed round a little bit until they saw the girls one had disappeared
the men wondered where she had gone the men saw bubbles coming up from the bottom of the lake they knew where one of the girls were at the bottom of the lake trying to find the way in the men made a plan
to try and get there before the girl get there one of the men said they might have a plan how to get into the castle
I will dive down and see where they get in then when they have gone we can go and explore the castle and ourselves there might be some hidden treasure then we will be rich richer then any on the world we can go for a month's holiday in Switzerland we needn't do any work until we die we can booze up
the other man said shut up they can hear you fool O ! shut up yourself you're making as much noise as me watch out someone has heard we better get going otherwise they'll think something fishy alright then will go The girls never knew about the two men they carried on with their work that night the two men went across the lake they knew where the hole is they had their swimming gear
they didn't not like that signpost with the skeleton on it looked a bit creepy a great wind rose it started thunder and lightning the two men were very scared the lake was getting very rough the boat started rock and it got very dangerous the men could not swim so they were very frightened the boat tipped over and the men fell out of the boat and drowned so they never got the treasure nor did the 4 spies it was only a rumour going round
but the castle was a mystery because there was an old lady dead in it the top of the tower She had been dead for 10 years no one knew this thing but the four spies explored the castle again they all went down in the water this time they weren't afraid of anything
they wanted to see if there was a witch living in the mystery castle they went up 3 towers and when they went up the 4 tower there was bats big spider crawling about the girls were a bit frightened they went up the creepy stairs and up the top was a big door with a key on the floor the door was locked one of the girls picked the key up and opened the door she was the bravest one she dared do anything the door was a bit stiff it grated as she opened it
It was absolutely horrified to find someone dead on the floor one of the girls fainted
they went near the old lady and saw it was a witch she had all black on and big finger nails nearly as big as a nail and as sharp as a pin She was as white and shrivelled up the girls left her there they locked the door and took the key with them so that no one will disturb her they never told anyone about this they kept the key for a souvenir and a memory of the mystery castle

Sudden Death
About 2 years ago there was a sudden death a lady named Misses Jones died of what no one knows
She washed their children's hair that night and her own then she went out to Mr Slad the grocer  and brought some fruit for the 4 children then she came back and talked to Mrs Clarke next door and after a while she came in got the children to bed then sat down and read a book called death on my Pillow she was laughing at some funny parts
then she decided to go to bed herself and in the middle of the might she went unconscious and that morning dad said good miring love and not a sound he said it again but no reply he got up and moved her about and she never woke up Mr Jones got worried and went up to the phone and rang up the doctor but the doctor was out somewhere so then he phoned up the hospital the ambulance came and took her to Melton hospital and doctor Nicholls said she is very ill we'll have to take her to Tonbury hospital they'll see what is the matter they rushed her there and after 2 days they hadn't had the proper things there so they took her to London hospital Mr Jones went to London with ambulance and stayed at London hospital for 3 days then he came home and waited for the bad or good news then on Monday morning at 5 o'clock a lady round the other side of us and came and gave us the bad news that she had died
and everyone very kind they gave us meals and two of children went and stayed with some friends for a week or two and now Mr Jones is getting married again and that will be better for the children

